  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Jude
      content: '  This letter is from Jude, a slave of Jesus Christ and a brother
        of James.I am writing to all who have been called by God the Father, who
        loves you and keeps you safe in the care of Jesus Christ.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Or <b>keeps you for Jesus Christ.</b>
    - title: The Danger of False Teachers
      content: 'May God give you more and more mercy, peace, and love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear friends, I had been eagerly planning to write to you about the
        salvation we all share. But now I find that I must write about something
        else, urging you to defend the faith that God has entrusted once for all
        time to his holy people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I say this because some ungodly people have wormed their way into
        your churches, saying that God\u2019s marvelous grace allows us to live immoral
        lives. The condemnation of such people was recorded long ago, for they have
        denied our only Master and Lord, Jesus Christ.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I want to remind you, though you already know these things, that
        Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] first rescued the nation of Israel from Egypt, but later
        he destroyed those who did not remain faithful. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>[the] Lord, </b>or <b>God, </b>or <b>God
          Christ.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And I remind you of the angels who did not stay within the limits
        of authority God gave them but left the place where they belonged. God has
        kept them securely chained in prisons of darkness, waiting for the great
        day of judgment. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t forget Sodom and Gomorrah and their neighboring towns,
        which were filled with immorality and every kind of sexual perversion. Those
        cities were destroyed by fire and serve as a warning of the eternal fire
        of God\u2019s judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the same way, these people\u2014who claim authority from their
        dreams\u2014live immoral lives, defy authority, and scoff at supernatural
        beings.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Greek <b>at glorious ones, </b>which are probably evil angels.
    - title: 
      content: "But even Michael, one of the mightiest of the angels,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        did not dare accuse the devil of blasphemy, but simply said, \u201CThe Lord
        rebuke you!\u201D (This took place when Michael was arguing with the devil
        about Moses\u2019 body.) "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: Greek <b>Michael, the archangel.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But these people scoff at things they do not understand. Like unthinking
        animals, they do whatever their instincts tell them, and so they bring about
        their own destruction. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow awaits them! For they follow in the footsteps of Cain,
        who killed his brother. Like Balaam, they deceive people for money. And like
        Korah, they perish in their rebellion.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When these people eat with you in your fellowship meals commemorating
        the Lord\u2019s love, they are like dangerous reefs that can shipwreck you.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        They are like shameless shepherds who care only for themselves. They are
        like clouds blowing over the land without giving any rain. They are like
        trees in autumn that are doubly dead, for they bear no fruit and have been
        pulled up by the roots. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: Or <b>they are contaminants among you; </b>or <b>they are stains.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They are like wild waves of the sea, churning up the foam of their
        shameful deeds. They are like wandering stars, doomed forever to blackest
        darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Enoch, who lived in the seventh generation after Adam, prophesied
        about these people. He said, \u201CListen! The Lord is coming with countless
        thousands of his holy ones "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "to execute judgment on the people of the world. He will convict every
        person of all the ungodly things they have done and for all the insults that
        ungodly sinners have spoken against him.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14-15 '
        content: 'The quotation comes from intertestamental literature: 1 Enoch 1:9.'
    - title: A Call to Remain Faithful
      content: 'These people are grumblers and complainers, living only to satisfy
        their desires. They brag loudly about themselves, and they flatter others
        to get what they want.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, my dear friends, must remember what the apostles of our
        Lord Jesus Christ predicted. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They told you that in the last times there would be scoffers whose
        purpose in life is to satisfy their ungodly desires. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These people are the ones who are creating divisions among you. They
        follow their natural instincts because they do not have God\u2019s Spirit
        in them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, dear friends, must build each other up in your most holy
        faith, pray in the power of the Holy Spirit,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: Greek <b>pray in the Holy Spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "and await the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ, who will bring you
        eternal life. In this way, you will keep yourselves safe in God\u2019s love.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you must show mercy to[[COMMENT(0)]] those whose faith is wavering. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:22 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>must reprove.</b>
    - title: A Prayer of Praise
      content: 'Rescue others by snatching them from the flames of judgment. Show
        mercy to still others,[[COMMENT(0)]] but do so with great caution, hating
        the sins that contaminate their lives.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:22-23a '
        content: 'Some manuscripts have only two categories of people: (1) those
          whose faith is wavering and therefore need to be snatched from the flames
          of judgment, and (2) those who need to be shown mercy.'
      - number: '1:23b '
        content: Greek <b>with fear, hating even the clothing stained by the flesh.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Now all glory to God, who is able to keep you from falling away and
        will bring you with great joy into his glorious presence without a single
        fault. '
      comments: []
